                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/15848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Earle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-15T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 15, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>427. The Secretary of the King informs me that the Germans are exerting heavy
                    pressure on King Boris to enter the war.</p>
                <p>He adds the King is doing his best to sidestep the issue and conciliate Germany
                    by making many comparatively unimportant concessions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
